[b]TVO The Agenda with Steve Paikin, February 27, 2008: William Kuebler on Omar Khadr | Ramin Jahanbegloo on Iran's notorious Evin Prison[/b]

1) [u]The Interview: William Kuebler[/u]

The last Westerner: Lt. Commander William Kuebler of the United States Navy Judge Advocate General's Corps on his client, Omar Khadr, and the Canadian government's refusal to seek his repatriation.

[b]William Kuebler[/b] is a lieutenant commander in the Judge Advocate General's Corps of the United States Navy. He has been detailed to the military commission cases of Ghassan Al Sharbi and Omar Khadr. Visit [url=http://www.defenselink.mil/news/commissions.html]United States Department of Defense - Military Commissions[/url] for more information.

